modules.description: Handles in-app browser interactions by providing methods to open, close, and manage web pages within a mobile application. Operates with URL strings, configuration records, and event callbacks. Used to display external content without leaving the app, such as loading a payment gateway or viewing an article.

This module provides functions to configure and customize in-app browser behavior, including setting presentation styles, transition animations, toolbar positions, and boolean flags for appearance and interaction. It works with custom types representing options and converts these configurations into executable strings for browser commands. Specific use cases include tailoring the browser's UI for different device orientations or enabling fullscreen mode in hybrid applications.
